{{About|numerological beliefs regarding the time 11:11||11:11 (disambiguation){{!}}11:11}}
[[File:11-11-11 on watch.jpg|200px|thumb|right|11-11-11 11:11:11 example]]
[[File:11-11-11 11-11 example.jpg|200px|thumb|right|11-11 11:11 example]]
Some [[numerologist]]s and [[New Age]] philosophies<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1111spiritguardians.com/ |title=Do you see 11:11? |publisher=11:11 Spirit Guardians |date= |accessdate=2011-11-11}}</ref> believe that events linked to the time '''11:11''' appear more often than can be explained by [[randomness|chance]] or [[coincidence]]<ref>Geller, Uri. [http://www.uri-geller.com/articles/11.htm "The 11:11 phenomenon."] 2006. Web. 22 Dec. 2014.</ref> and is an example of [[synchronicity]]. Some authors claim that seeing 11:11 on a clock is an auspicious sign.{{Citation needed|date=May 2015}} Others claim that 11:11 signals a spirit presence.<ref>{{cite book |last=Solara  |title=11:11: Inside the Doorway |year=1992 |publisher=Star-Borne Unlimited |isbn=1-878246-05-4 |location=Charlottesville, VA}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=George Barnard  |title=The Search for 11:11: A Journey into the Spirit World |year=2004 |publisher=11:11 Publishers |isbn=0-9577889-6-7 |location=Australia}}</ref> However, skeptics say that [[Uri Geller]]'s examples of 11:11 phenomena in world events are examples of [[post hoc theorizing|post-hoc]] reasoning<ref>{{cite web|url=http://skepticreport.com/sr/?p=519 |title=Uri Geller |accessdate=2009-10-05 |quote=On his web site, Uri Geller has a list of things he connects with the number 11. He believes this number to be all-important. E.g. he attaches meaning to the fact that some people have noticed their clocks sometimes show the numbers "11:11". |publisher=Skeptic Report |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5kNDgTNJX?url=http://skepticreport.com/sr/?p=519 |archivedate=8 October 2009 |deadurl=no |df=dmy }}</ref> and [[confirmation bias]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://skepdic.com/lawofnumbers.html |title=The law of truly large numbers |accessdate=2009-11-21 |quote=The law of truly large numbers says that with a large enough sample many odd coincidences are likely to happen. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091202210107/http://skepdic.com/lawofnumbers.html |archivedate=2 December 2009 |deadurl=no |df=dmy }}</ref>

== Significance in dates ==
For various reasons, people ascribe different kinds of significance to dates and numbers; for example, the date of November 11, 2011, or "11/11/11", showed an increase in the number of [[marriage]]s taking place in different areas throughout the world, including the U.S.<ref name="US 11-11-11 Marriages">{{cite web|title=11/11/11: 'Ones' in a lifetime|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2011-11-10/living/living_eleven-eleven-eleven_1_phone-numbers-carlson-special-celebration?_s=PM:LIVING|author=Basu, Moni|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2011-11-11|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111111202621/http://articles.cnn.com/2011-11-10/living/living_eleven-eleven-eleven_1_phone-numbers-carlson-special-celebration?_s=PM%3ALIVING|archivedate=11 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and across the Asian continent.<ref name="Asian 11-11-11 Marriages">{{cite web| title=11/11/11 spells marriage and magic| url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/RestOfAsia/11-11-11-spells-marriage-and-magic/Article1-768016.aspx| author=Savadove, Bill| publisher=Hindustan Times| accessdate=2011-11-11| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111112050116/http://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/RestOfAsia/11-11-11-spells-marriage-and-magic/Article1-768016.aspx| archivedate=12 November 2011| df=dmy-all}}</ref> Many females were pregnant at this time, and babies born on this date also received special media attention.<ref name="11-11-11 Baby">{{cite web|title=11/11/11 baby born at 11:11 a.m. on LI|url=http://www.newsday.com/long-island/nassau/11-11-11-baby-born-at-11-11-a-m-on-li-1.3314338| author=Murphy, William| publisher=Newsday| accessdate=2011-11-11}}</ref>

