{{multiple| {{Orphan|date=August 2017}} {{cleanup reorganize|date=August 2017}} }} [[File:Aleksandra Pawliszyn obraz.jpg|thumb]] '''Aleksandra Pawliszyn''' (born 30 December 1958) is a Polish philosopher, specializing in the areas of [[Phenomenology (philosophy)|phenomenology]] and [[philosophical hermeneutics]].
She obtained her doctorate in 1991 at [[Warsaw University]] on the basis of a work titled: ''Czynności rozumienia w hermeneutyce Gadamerai psychoanalizie Freuda''<!-- The content of this particular work was consulted in correspondence with Hans-Georg Gadamer. Its publication was subsidized by the Ministry of National Education. -->, and qualified as an assistant professor in 2002, also at Warsaw University, on the basis of a work titled: ''Krajobrazyczasu. Obecne dociekania egzystencjalnej wartości czasu''. For a period of eight years she was head of The Department of Learning Theory at the Institute of Philosophy, Sociology and Journalism at [[Gdansk University]]. From 2015 she has been a member of the International Husserl and Phenomenology Research Society (USA).
