'''Luis Carlos Restrepo Ramírez''' (born 24 January 1954) is a Colombian psychiatrist and philosopher, who served as the 5th [[High Commissioner for Peace (Colombia)|High Commissioner for Peace of Colombia]] from August 2002 to March 2009.

While in Office, he was in charge of the controversial demobilization and disarmament of 32,000 paramilitaries of the [[United Self-Defense Forces of Colombia]] and 13,000 guerrilla fighters.<ref name=justiciao>{{cite web|title=Justicia o persecución?|url=http://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/justicia-persecucion/253313-3/|publisher=[[Revista Semana]]|accessdate=1 July 2016|date=11 July 2012}}</ref>

For some time, the [[Government of Colombia]] considered him a [[fugitive]],<ref name=pettesson>{{cite web|last=Ohlsen Pettersson|first=Olle |title=Arrest warrant confirmed for Colombia’s ex-peace commissioner|url=http://colombiareports.com/arrest-warrant-confirmed-for-colombias-ex-peace-commissioner/|publisher=Colombia Reports|accessdate=4 July 2013|date=30 July 2012}}</ref><ref name=dondeesta>{{cite journal|title=¿Dónde está Luis Carlos Restrepo?|journal=[[Semana]]|date=19 January 2013|url=http://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/donde-esta-luis-carlos-restrepo/330074-3|accessdate=4 July 2013|location=Bogotá|language=Spanish|issn=0124-5473|oclc=7475329}}</ref><ref name=dondeesta>{{cite journal|title=Juez ordena captura de Luis Carlos Restrepo|journal=[[Semana]]|date=9 February 2012|url=http://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/juez-ordena-captura-luis-carlos-restrepo/253160-3|accessdate=4 July 2013|location=Bogotá|language=Spanish|issn=0124-5473|oclc=7475329}}</ref> after the [[Supreme Court of Justice of Colombia]] issued an international [[arrest warrant]]<ref name=pettesson/><ref name=dondeesta/> after Restrepo left the country on {{date|2012-01-08}} on a flight bound to the [[United States]];<ref name=pettesson/><ref name=dondeesta/><ref name=dondeesta/> his current whereabouts remain unknown, but he is presumed to have obtained [[political asylum]] in Canada.<ref name=asylum>{{cite web|title=Luis Carlos Restrepo consiguió asilo en Canadá|url=http://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/luis-carlos-restrepo-consiguio-asilo-en-canada/402054-3|publisher=[[Revista Semana]]|accessdate=1 July 2016|date=14 August 2014}}</ref>
Restrepo, who was accused of faking the [[demobilization]] of a [[FARC]] [[military unit]] in 2006,<ref name=pettesson/><ref name=dondeesta/><ref name=dondeesta/> is charged by the [[Office of the Attorney General of Colombia]] with [[Conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy to commit crime]]; [[embezzlement]]; and arms [[Weapon possession|possession]], [[Arms trafficking|trafficking]], and manufacturing.<ref name=dondeesta/> Restrepo, who was one of the closest allies of the President [[Álvaro Uribe Vélez]],<ref name=pettesson/><ref name=dondeesta/><ref name=dondeesta/> has denied the allegations made against him, and accused the Administration of President [[Juan Manuel Santos Calderón]] of mounting a [[political persecution]] against him; in this he receives the backing and support of former President Uribe.<ref name=pettesson/> However, on September 23, 2013, Colombia's Prosecutor General dropped the arrest warrant against Restrepo.<ref>http://colombiareports.co/colombia-drops-arrest-warrants-former-peace-commissioner/</ref>

From his exile, Restrepo has shown support for the current Peace talks of President [[Juan Manuel Santos]] with [[FARC]] rebels.<ref name=peaceSantos>{{cite web|title=Santos pide a uribistas escuchar a Restrepo|url=http://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/santos-respalda-luis-carlos-restrepo/413129-3|publisher=[[Revista Semana]]|accessdate=1 July 2016|date=22 December 2014}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Luis Carlos was born on 24 January 1954 in [[Filandia]], [[Caldas Department]] to Carlos E. Restrepo Ramírez and Soledad Ramírez Ospina.

